The paper discusses a reinforcement learning approach for robots to acquire skills while ensuring safety. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach involves hierarchical task optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The safety aspect is also related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the validation of the approach involves simulations and real-world experiments with grasping, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
